<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-225-062 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 406 620</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Feb 8 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>UK: Grid moves to new European headquarters. (Grid ComputerSystems)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Grid Systems Corp. (Headquarters).andO;Topic:     Computer industryEuropeFacility LocationEngland.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>UK: GRID MOVES TO NEW EUROPEAN HEADQUARTERS 02/08/91 HEATHROW, MIDDLESEX,ENGLAND, 1991 JAN 8 (NB) -- Grid Computer Systems, part of the Intertan(Radio Shack) group, has opened new headquarters near Heathrow Airport in theUK.andP;  The new premises are to provide the rapid growth the company isexperiencing, as well as providing for customer training needs.andM;&quot;Our rapid growth during 1990 has not only been in the UK, but also inEurope.andP;  Being located on the perimeter of Heathrow airport will easecommunication with our pan-European customers and world-wide offices,&quot;explained Mike Daly, Grid's managing director.andM;&quot;We feel that these new premises provide us with the highest level offacilities for our growing user base.andP;  Furthermore, we now have the space tocontinue our predicted expansion during the 1990s,&quot; he added.andM;Grid's new premises, which opened this week, provide the company with 9,000square feet of office space and more than 20,000 square feet of warehousingspace.andM;Grid Computer Systems currently employs more than 550 staff worldwide.andP;  Thecompany is best-known for its Gridcase series of laptops, one of which - theGridcase 1500 - is the only laptops to be used in space by NASA.andM;(Steve Gold/19910108/Press andamp; Public Contact: Grid Computer Systems - Tel:081-897-6565)</TEXT></DOC>